snippet.textDisplay:
Shannon can do some jive talking for sure but he damn sure isnt a know it all about Football.

Look , Brady , Belicheck, and the Pats have had trouble with Miami for as long as Brady has been the starter . I am not surprised they lost this game at all . Its happened before , a couple years ago in fact . Patriots still went to the Superbowl .

Look , when youve had so much success as The Pats have had for years, they can get complacent ok .They are still 12-4 . Most teams would love to have that record .Im sure the Browns or Indy would love to be 12-4 . The Pats reciever core is trash tho . Edellman is their only real gladiator . Sanu hasnt really been a difference maker . You would think as smart as the Pats are they would be out working the phones all season to get a TE replacement for Gronk in trade. Maybe Mason Rudolph or someone of his talent ? They didnt , and Brady is suffering for it . I feel Belichek has been purposefully trading or cutting Tom's recievers away to push him out of New England . Last season's Superbowl win wasnt really expected I believe . Belichek would take it tho of course . When Tom leaves New England the public will be surprised that Belichek all of the sudden loads up on talented recievers for his backup QB to be able to thrive right away . New England wont be in rebuild mode when Tom leaves . They will still be in Superbowl mode . Tom will wonder why he didnt get the reciever core his replacement is getting , will be the headline. Then Tom will either join the Jets or Miami to get back at Belichek .

snippet.textDisplay:
Really cute how Skip thinks the world goes as he thinks it will - but he quite obviously never even gave a passing thought about why the Chargers would want to replace a badly aging QB who is at least familiar with the system and the roster, with a much older and even more badly aging QB who has never been part of that roster and has never shown that he can be a good QB outside the only system he's ever played in, and which has been tailored and finetuned to him 100%...
I have a hard time trying to find a level on which it would make the slightest sense.

snippet.textDisplay: The offensive line hasn't been all that bad this season -- just injured more often than not. You'd probably have to go back to 2006 to find a comparably bad receiving corps, but even that team had enough going for it elsewhere to upset (with some luck) the top-seeded Chargers and hold a 21-3 lead late in the AFC CG on the road against Peyton Manning's Colts. Maybe they survive the Titans this week, but I don't think they have the firepower to go into Arrowhead and come out with a win again.
